CHUKWUJEKWU ILOZUE; CHARLES ONYEKAMUO AWKA – Most Rev. Paulinus Chukwue­meka Ezeokafor, the Catholic Bishop of Awka has urged the Federal Government to diversify the economy for the survival of the people lament­ing that the economy is run on “hit and run basis”, while advanced nations plan their ahead. Bishop Ezeokafor made the statement in his Christ­mas and New Year message in Awka on Thursday observed that with the country run­ning into recession for a sec­ond time in one year, did not need to run a mono economy but should exploit it numer­ous resources and look into its agricultural potentials for survival. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said that government in power must work to improve the standard of living of the masses and be prepared to hand over to younger people. He warned that if this is not done, there may be second wave of ENDSARS which this time may be “End of big men with no visible source of liv­ing”. Yuletide: Gov. Ugwuanyi Prays For Divine Intervention $311m Abacha Loot: FG Approves CSO To Monitor Project Execution He also asked the govern­ment to be conscious of bor­rowing for non productive sec­tor so as not impose hardship on the coming generation. He criticised border clo­sure which lasted for 16 months saying the country has not gained anything from it. He said: “I am not comfort­able with the closure of bor­ders for 16 months. To make the matter worse, not all the borders were closed. Besides, what have we gained from the closure, he queried. Also speaking on the security situation in the country, Ezeokafor won­dered why both President Muhammadu Buhari has not resigned having failed to achieve the promise he made to the electorate to se­cure the nation. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO S